{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper. Grease 6 dariole moulds (Ø 7 cm) with oil and sprinkle with sugar then set aside.","Place bread in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place 200 g onions, carrots, 3 garlic cloves, olives, celery, coriander, 25 g olive oil and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl then chop <b>7 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add tofu, flour and reserved breadcrumbs then mix <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Form into 20 balls then place on prepared baking tray and cook for 20-30 minutes (200°C) until browned, covering and setting aside once done. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and continue with recipe.","Place cassava in mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add coconut milk, sugar, oil and cornflour then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add coconut and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Divide mixture between prepared moulds and place in Varoma dish then cover with Varoma lid and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place water and remaining 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl.","Insert simmering basket and weigh in rice. Place Varoma into position then steam <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Remove Varoma and unmould quindim. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Reserve 190 g cooking water and discard rest. Transfer cooked rice to a serving bowl. Pour over reserved cooking water and stir with spatula. Cover to keep warm.","Place remaining 1 garlic clove, 100 g onions and 30 g olive oil in mixing bowl, chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add spinach, peas and carrots then sauté <b>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to serving bowl with rice and stir together with spatula. Serve vegetable rice with tofu meatballs. Enjoy quindims for dessert."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["70 g stale white bread, torn in pieces","300 g onions, quartered","150 g carrots, cut in pieces","4 garlic cloves","20 g pitted black olives","20 g celery stalk, cut in pieces","10 g fresh coriander","55 g olive oil","2 tsp fine sea salt","200 g tofu, diced","50 g plain flour","400 g cassava, cut in pieces","260 g coconut milk","180 g sugar, plus extra for sprinkling","15 g sunflower oil, plus extra for greasing","30 g cornflour","100 g desiccated coconut","1200 g water","250 g brown rice","150 g frozen spinach, defrosted, drained","100 g frozen green peas","100 g baby carrots, sliced"]}],"id":"r134387","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-QZ4VypOYQrM\/XZVRRfFr8bI\/AAAAAAAAdMI\/_FZqYdmIJZMYi9XaQZIn10omYB5cv3n2gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kBY-dm79tH1w13HY.png","title":"Tofu Meatballs with Rice and Vegan Quindim","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16 g","fat":"35 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"157 g","calories":"4678 kJ \/ 1118 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and baking paper, jug, serving bowl, cling film, dariole moulds, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Quindim is a classic Brazilian dessert made of set coconut and custard. Typically presented as an upturned cup, it is dense with a glistening appearance and is intensely sweet and addictive!"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 35m","6 portions"]}